Expected result (if the rendertarget isn't changed or by running on WinGL):
![expected](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/9132168/7010629/ac5496ce-dc9a-11e4-9c23-981b7e7f8fc0.png)

However if the rendertarget swap occurs the image will quickly flash and then nothing gets renderered. It appears that the current samplers state aren't getting properly apply.

Adding the following line after setting the shader parameters "fixes" the issue:

``` C#
GraphicsDevice.Textures[1] = null;
```

Since the shaders values are passed to device inside the apply() during the spritebatch operation, the, it appears by setting texture in s1 to null we are setting some dirty flag that isn't properly set when the rendertarget swap occurs.

More information in the following link:
http://community.monogame.net/t/issue-with-spritebach-and-custom-shaders/2196

